.*A*                                                            
This help file contains an overview of the CP-6 X Account.  The X account is
the repository of useful programs that have been written by the developers and
customers of CP-6.  This help file separates the tools into logical categories.
These categories are:  DOCUMENTATION, EDUCATIONAL, GRAPHICS, INTEGRATION,
MICROPROCESSOR, GENERAL, OFFICE_AUTOMATION, PROGRAMMING, PROGRAMMING_LANGUAGE,
PROJECT_MANAGEMENT, SUPPORT, SYSTEM_MANAGEMENT, SYSTEM_PROGRAMMING, and
UTILITY.
.*R*
To obtain a list of the tools under each category, type:
.*R*
   HELP (XINDEX.X) category
 
This help file also contains abstracts that briefly describe the tools.  To
view an abstract, type:
   HELP (XINDEX.X) ABSTRACTS toolname
 
This help file also contains separates the tools according to keywords.  These
keywords assist you in locating tools.  To obtain a list of keywords, type:
   HELP (XINDEX.X) KEYWORDS TOPICS
 
To obtain a list of tools that belong to any keyword, type:
.*R*
   HELP (XINDEX.X) KEYWORDS keyword
 
To obtain complete information about any tool, type:
.*R*
   HELP (tool.X)
.*R*
.*K* CHANGES
12/19/85 Added to X account.
.*K* XINDEX_ABSTRACT
TOOL=XINDEX
.*R*
This is the index for the entire X account.
.*K* XINDEX
